# CODEOWNERS — release pipeline & native build files
#
# GitLab and GitHub both honor a top-level CODEOWNERS file. Listed
# owners are auto-requested as reviewers on any MR/PR that touches the
# matching paths. On GitLab Premium these can be marked as
# "Protected" code owners, which blocks merge until the owner approves
# — recommended for everything below.
#
# Why this file exists: CI/release files have been silently rolled
# back in feature-branch merge conflict resolutions. Adding owners
# makes any changes to these paths visible during review and prevents
# the iOS pipeline / signing logic / Capacitor pins from being
# accidentally reverted.
#
# CI / release pipelines
/.github/workflows/                    @guidedgrowthplatform
/.gitlab-ci.yml                        @guidedgrowthplatform

# iOS native build, signing, fastlane
/fastlane/                             @guidedgrowthplatform
/capacitor.config.ts                   @guidedgrowthplatform
/scripts/patch-ios-plist.mjs           @guidedgrowthplatform
/scripts/cartesia-line-agent/          @guidedgrowthplatform

# Capacitor / native dependency pins
# (the SPM pin and pre-8.1.x plugin compatibility is load-bearing —
# changes here usually require revisiting the native build flow)
/package.json                          @guidedgrowthplatform
/package-lock.json                     @guidedgrowthplatform

# Release docs (so handoff to the team stays accurate)
/docs/RELEASE.md                       @guidedgrowthplatform
/CODEOWNERS                            @guidedgrowthplatform
